1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 packet Sweet Chilli Sauce
600 g Pork Loin Steaks
1 Cucumber
1 Lime
1 packet Cherry Tomatoes
1 drizzle olive oil

• Thinly slice cucumber into half moons. Halve cherry tomatoes.
• Cut lime into wedges.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Season pork on both sides with salt and pepper.
• When oil is hot, cook pork steaks until cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Transfer to a plate, cover and rest for 5 minutes.

• Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine sweet chilli sauce, a good squeeze of lime juice and a drizzle of olive oil.
• Add cherry tomatoes, cucumber and mixed salad leaves to the dressing, tossing to coat. Season to taste.

• Divide pork steaks and zingy cucumber salad between plates.
• Garnish with crispy shallots. Serve with any remaining lime wedges. Enjoy!